fusion about module boundaries. **Mitigation**: Remove if no direct code dependency exists, or add a comment explaining why it is needed.\\\\\\\\n- **Nickname logged at debug level (JuheQqIdentityProvider.java:160)**: `logger.debugf(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"juhe-qq: user info retrieved uid=*** nick=%s\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", nickname)` — logging the nickname is very low risk but could theoretically log user-provided content. **Mitigation**: Acceptable as-is since it's `debug` level and nickname is not secret, but add a comment acknowledging the choice.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### BLOCKERS\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nNone.\\\\\\\",\\\",\\n      \\\"context_before\\\": [\\n        \\\"      \\\\\\\"nickname\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"喙鲸\\\\\\\",\\\",\\n        \\\"      \\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Completed\\\\\\\",\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"context_after\\\": [\\n        \\\"      \\\\\\\"steps_taken\\\\\\\": 7,\\\",\\n        \\\"      \\\\\\\"checkpoint\\\\\\\": {\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"file\\\": \\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\?\\\\\\\\C:\\\\\\\\Users\\\\\\\\yu.chen\\\\\\\\Desktop\\\\\\\\MyPersonalProject\\\\\\\\WotbTools\\\\\\\\.deepseek\\\\\\\\state\\\\\\\\subagents.v1.json\\\",\\n      \\\"line_number\\\": 417,\\n      \\\"line\\\": \\\"                \\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"FROM quay.io/keycloak/keycloak:26.6.4\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nCOPY docker/keycloak/keycloak-juhe-qq-provider.jar /opt/keycloak/providers/\\\\\\\\nCOPY docker/keycloak/keycloak-social-provider-china-1.0.0.jar /opt/keycloak/providers/\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nRUN /opt/keycloak/bin/kc.sh build\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n      \\\"context_before\\\": [\\n        \\\"                \\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"tool_result\\\\\\\",\\\",\\n        \\\"                \\\\\\\"tool_use_id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"call_06_RSGrZ9CijgpyjDUZAL608603\\\\\\\",\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"context_after\\\": [\\n        \\\"              },\\\",\\n        \\\"              {\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"file\\\": \\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\?\\\\