seAuth.js:10-13` — The Keycloak URL is hard-coded to `https://auth.wotbtools.com`. This prevents local/offline development where Keycloak runs on `http://localhost:8080`. There is no environment variable or build-time configuration to override this.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  - **PROBLEM C**: `java/keycloak-juhe-qq-provider/pom.xml:43-47` — The `keycloak-services` dependency at scope `provided` is unusual; typically `keycloak-server-spi-private` is sufficient. However, since the code only references classes from `keycloak-server-spi` and `keycloak-server-spi-private` (no direct `keycloak-services` types), this is likely harmless but slightly over-broad.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### CHANGES\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nNone.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### RISKS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Broken Docker build (docker/Dockerfile.keycloak:2)**: The `COPY` of `keycloak-juhe-qq-provider.jar` will fail because the jar is never built and does not exist in the source tree. **Mitigation**: Add a multi-stage build step in the Dockerfile to build the provider jar from source (similar to how `Dockerfile.backend` builds the backend), or pre-build and commit the jar, or modify the Dockerfile to reference the jar from the Maven build output.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Hard-coded production Keycloak URL (frontend/src/composables/useAuth.js:11)**: Local developers must manually edit this file to test against a local Keycloak instance. **Mitigation**: Use a build-time environment variable (e.g., Vite `import.meta.env.VITE_KEYCLOAK_URL`) with the production URL as default but overridable in `.env.development`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Unused keycloak-services dependency (pom.xml:43-47)**: While harmless at `provided` scope, it creates a minor maintenance burden and potential confusion about module boundaries. **Mitigation**: Remove if no direct code dependency exists, or add a comment explaining why it is needed.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- **Nickname logged at debug level (JuheQqIdentityProvider.java:160)**: `logger.debugf(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"juhe-qq: user info retrieved uid=*** nick=%s\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", nickname)` — logging the nickname is very low risk but could theoretically log user-provided content. **Mitigation**: Acceptable as-is since it's `debug` level and nickname is not secret, but add a comment acknowledging the choice.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### BLOCKERS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nNone.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n      \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"context_before\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"      \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed_at_ms\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 1782729387949,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"      \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"latest_message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n      ],\\\\\\\\n      \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"context_after\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"      \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"steps_taken\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 7,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"      \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"events\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n      ]\\\\\\\\n    },\\\\\\\\n    {\\\\\\\\n      \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"file\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\C:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\Users\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\yu.chen\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\Desktop\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\MyPersonalProject\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\