cal variables and method parameters use `final`**: CONFIRMED PASS. Every method parameter in all three Java files uses `final` (e.g., `JuheQqIdentityProvider.java:37` constructor, :43 `performLogin`, :97 `callback`, :204 `encode`, :208 `isBlank`). All local variables use `final` (e.g., `appid`, `appkey`, `loginBaseUrl`, `callbackUrl`, `actLoginUrl`, `httpReq`, `httpResp`, `json`, `code`, `type`, `redirectUrl`, `nickname`, `faceimg`, etc.). Factory parameters and config constructor also use `final`.\\n- **Item 4 — Error handling covers all spec-required scenarios**: CONFIRMED PASS. `JuheQqIdentityProvider.java:48-53` — handles missing appid/appkey/loginBaseUrl in performLogin. `:72-75` — handles non-200 HTTP response in act=login. `:82-85` — handles API response code != 0, type != \\\"qq\\\", or empty redirect URL. `:90-93` — catches `IOException | InterruptedException` for network errors. `:104-112` — validates callback type=qq and non-empty code. `:120-123` — re-validates credentials in callback (defense-in-depth). `:139-142` — handles non-200 HTTP in callback. `:149-153` — validates callback response code/type/uid. `:187-189` — catches IO/InterruptedException in callback.\\n- **Item 5 — Logging only non-sensitive information**: CONFIRMED PASS with minor caveat. All log statements log only `code`, `type`, `nickname` (non-sensitive), and `social_uid` masked as `***` (line 151). However `JuheQqIdentityProvider.java:150-151` logs `uid=%s` where the value is `(empty)` or `***` — this is fine. Also logs `nickname` at line 160 which is user-provided but not secret. **Minor risk**: logging `nickname` is acceptable but could contain user-provided special characters; no PII issue.\\n- **Item 6 — Configuration / deployment / integration integrity**: FOUND 3 PROBLEMS.\\n  - **PROBLEM A**: `docker/Dockerfile.keycloak:2` — `COPY docker/keycloak/keycloak-juhe-qq-provider.jar /opt/keycloak/providers/` references a file that does **not exist** in `docker/keycloak/`. The directory 